        <svcsubproc id="s305010706.1.2">
            <title>AMS Operation</title>
            <para id="s305010706.1.2.1">
                <title>Function</title>
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Dual stage turbocharger</title>
            </para>
            <para>The dual stage turbocharger responds directly to engine loads. Different engine loads affect exhaust
                energy that determines turbocharger speed. Turbocharger speed controls boost pressure for various engine
                loads. The dual stages of the turbocharger contribute to the lowering of exhaust emissions.
            </para>
            <para>At engine low idle, engine load and boost are low. As engine rpm increases, more fuel and air enter
                the cylinders. Exhaust temperature and pressure increase; higher exhaust energy increases turbine and
                compressor speed that raises the pressure and temperature of inlet boost air .
            </para>
            <para>As engine rpm and load decrease, less fuel and air enter the cylinders. Exhaust temperature and
                pressure decrease; lower exhaust energy decreases turbine and compressor speed that lowers the pressure
                and temperature of boost air.
            </para>
            <para>The Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR) system controls the amount of exhaust gas being introduced to the
                intake manifold. When the EGR is commanded, the EGR valve opens allowing cooled exhaust gases to enter
                the intake manifold to be mixed with filtered intake air. The mixed air is then is recycled through
                combustion process. The EGR actuator is located at the front of the engine on the intake manifold.
            </para>
            <para>The EGR drive module controls the actuator motor and is chassis mounted near the IDM and ECM
                modules.
            </para>
            <para>The ECM calculates the appropriate desired EGR valve position in response to the changing engine
                speed, fuel desired, operator demand, engine operating temperatures, boost pressure and altitude.
            </para>
            <table id="t305010710" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>The ECM uses sensor input from the following:</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Accelerator Position Sensor (APS)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>EGR actuator with position sensors</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>EGR drive module</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Mass Air Flow (MAF) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Manifold Absolute Temperature (MAT) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Barometric Absolute Pressure (BAP) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Engine Coolant Temperature (ECT) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Engine Coolant Level (ECL) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Engine Oil Temperature (EOT) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Manifold Absolute Pressure (MAP) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>The EGR drive module provides feedback to the ECM on the valve position. The EGR drive module
                interprets the ECM command and sends the command using three pulse width modulated signals to the valve
                actuator.
            </para>
            <para>The system is closed loop control using the EGR position signals. The EGR drive module provides a 9
                volt supply and ground to the Integrated Circuit (IC) in the motor of the valve. When the EGR drive
                module directs the valve to move, the IC with three Hall effect sensors provides the EGR drive module
                with the valve position signals. The EGR drive module interprets the three signals to determine valve
                position and sends the information back to the ECM.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Fault Detection/Management</title>The ECM continuously monitors the Air Management System (AMS).
                When the ECM detects a fault in any of the interdependent systems. The ECM will set a DTC and illuminate
                the amber caution lamp.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">The Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR)</emph>
                actuator is continuously monitored by the EGR drive module. When an EGR control error is detected, the
                EGR drive module sends a message to the ECM, a DTC is set, and the amber caution lamp is illuminated.
                For additional function and operational information, see "
                <hotlnk document="eges3052_143.xml" xrefid="s305010706.15.1.1">EGR (Exhaust Gas Recirculation) Control
                </hotlnk>
                " in this section.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>AMS DTCs</title>DTCs are read using the EST or by counting the flashes from the amber caution and
                red warning lamps.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Before proceeding, make sure all sensor, injector, and actuator electrical DTCs have been
                        repaired. Follow the procedures outlined in the "
                        <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050106.xml" xrefid="e3050106">Performance Diagnostics</hotlnk>
                        " section of this manual or Performance Diagnostics Form.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t305010711" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>DTC 343</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.78*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.22*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col2" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Excessive exhaust back pressure</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>This is an estimated value expressing excessive cylinder pressures based off of
                                    boost pressure.
                                </para>
                                <para>MAP is continuously monitored through out the engine operation. DTC 343 is set
                                    when MAP is greater than expected.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Possible Causes</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Turbocharger boost control (TCBC) system failure</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Do "
                                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050106.xml" xrefid="e3050106">Performance Diagnostics
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    Step 12 Boost Control."
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Biased high MAP sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>See "
                                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_158.xml" xrefid="s305010706.29.1.1">MAP Operational
                                        Diagnostics
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    " in this section.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <table id="t305010712" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>DTC 346</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="3.00*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Faults detected during EGR portion of the AMS Test</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>DTC 346 is set by the ECM during AMS test when the ECM measures MAF and does not
                                    see the expected response in MAF.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Possible Causes</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>EGR valve stuck or sticking</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Do "
                                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050106.xml" xrefid="e3050106">Performance Diagnostics
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    ."
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>MAF sensor bias</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Check sensor signal frequency. See "
                                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_157.xml" xrefid="s305010706.28.1.1.1">MAF circuit
                                        diagnostics
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    ."
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Obstruction in air inlet to MAF sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Do "
                                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050106.xml" xrefid="e3050106">Performance Diagnostics
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    ."
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>EGR control circuit</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Check sensor signal frequency. See "
                                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_143.xml" xrefid="s305010706.15.2.1">EGR circuit
                                        diagnostics
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    ."
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Plugged air filter</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Do "
                                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050106.xml" xrefid="e3050106">Performance Diagnostics
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    ."
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Loose clamps for induction system (MAF sensor to turbocharger)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Do "
                                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050106.xml" xrefid="e3050106">Performance Diagnostics
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    ."
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Exhaust leaks (engine to turbocharger)</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Do "
                                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050106.xml" xrefid="e3050106">Performance Diagnostics
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    ."
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Plugged Exhaust system</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Do "
                                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050106.xml" xrefid="e3050106">Performance Diagnostics
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    ."
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
